article.headline: McNeese State 79, Texas State 67
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. (AP) -- Jerrick Oliver and Greg Tucker each scored 17 points as McNeese State took a 79-67 victory over Texas State on Saturday. Tucker was 10-of-10 from the free throw line, Oliver grabbed 10 rebounds and Edward Garriet hit five 3-pointers to finish with 16 points for McNeese (9-16, 5-9 Southland Conference). McNeese led 36-33 at halftime, then shot 57 percent in the second half to pull away. Texas State (12-13, 7-7) shot only 37 percent for the game. Terry Conerway led Texas State with 13 points, while Roosevelt Brown added 12 and Josh Naylor 11. <
